{"version":"2.0","workflows": [],"nodes":[{"id":"fe77864d-bfd1-4c9e-99b6-41c97f9e63fe","type":"note","position":{"x":650,"y":270},"size":{"width":510,"height":260},"type_specific":{"message":"My role at [my company] is [my job].\n\nSome character traits the mail should convey:\n- I work strictly towards results\n- I am direct and to the point\n- I am honest, I dislike phrases or deferrals\n- I always use simple, easy to understand language\n- I want to keep my emails as short as humanly possible, concise and precise\n- I don't like conditional sentences with lots of \"could\" and \"would\"","title":"Addtitional background on myself","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"d96f3797-7334-4f09-ac60-e0579cfa591d","type":"bot","position":{"x":1620,"y":1270},"size":{"width":380,"height":454},"type_specific":{"prompt_input":"Create a summary / follow-up email to all participants of the meeting with the specific purpose of [xyz]","prompt_output":"","state":"success","split_size":[15.09693488726556,84.90306511273444],"auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"353224db-857e-4e38-98aa-964418562c1b","type":"note","position":{"x":-570,"y":-250},"size":{"width":410,"height":360},"type_specific":{"message":"","title":"Example 2","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"4f380c94-0b86-41ef-a513-2c25fc6b23f6","type":"bot","position":{"x":850,"y":660},"size":{"width":400,"height":406},"type_specific":{"prompt_input":"Now you also have as background some indications on how the writer wants to come across. Use these, alongside your analysis results of the writers previous texts to make improvement proposals. Again, make sure your very specific to the case at hand!\nKeep it short and make it so that an AI model can recognize and utilize the important patters from your response","prompt_output":"","state":"success","split_size":[27.442987621283354,72.55701237871665],"auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"6dc49714-cb64-4230-8680-a6eb25c3cedb","type":"bot","position":{"x":250,"y":660},"size":{"width":440,"height":413},"type_specific":{"prompt_input":"In the context, you will find examples of email correspondence. Read several documents authored by the user (emails, chat histories, letters, etc.) and extract the writing style. Then formalize the writing style in a style guide and return it.","prompt_output":"","state":"success","split_size":[28.977893710922764,71.02210628907724],"auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"b2fe3163-eb54-4df9-b01d-59cdca796069","type":"note","position":{"x":-40,"y":110},"size":{"width":500,"height":434},"type_specific":{"message":"- Full name: e.g. Prof. Dr. Maximilian Musterfrau S.J. \n- Salutation and greeting\n    - Formal, e.g. \"Dear Professor...\"\n    - Friendly and businesslike at the same time, e.g. \"Hello...\"\n    - Friendly, e.g. \"Servus...\"\n- Introductory sentences; e.g. \"Thank you very much for your e-mail!\"\n- Linguistic style:\n    - Sentence structure and complexity\n    - Focus on hypotactic vs. paratactic sentence structure\n    - Sentence length\n    - Frequency of use of bullet point lists in enumerations    \n    - Length of paragraphs \n    - Use of active vs. passive formulations \n- Recurring patterns\n- Additional notes\n\n","title":"Structure: Style guide","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"0e0884ac-2754-41ff-81d3-cbe4ea15c64e","type":"frame","position":{"x":-1070,"y":-297},"size":{"width":970,"height":882},"type_specific":{"color":"note-color-3"}},{"id":"4ea34c0a-e2ca-46ec-b1ec-0712dc2ba56b","type":"note","position":{"x":-1020,"y":-250},"size":{"width":410,"height":360},"type_specific":{"message":"","title":"Example  1","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"ef45d350-a25f-453a-bd11-8e33593a4aa5","type":"note","position":{"x":-570,"y":160},"size":{"width":410,"height":360},"type_specific":{"message":"","title":"Example 4","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"259b54cc-cba6-4fb1-a46c-68b830d71d4a","type":"note","position":{"x":-1020,"y":160},"size":{"width":410,"height":360},"type_specific":{"message":"","title":"Example 3","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"cc23805f-5aa5-462f-b0b1-cfcb3c50d2c9","type":"bot","position":{"x":250,"y":1230},"size":{"width":660,"height":440},"type_specific":{"prompt_input":"To enable a bit of quantitative dialing of the tonality and content of a text, extract the most important aspects of a text, given the background of the writer. For each aspect, give a ranking, how important it is for the purpose of the text and how well it is implemented in the previous texts by the writer","prompt_output":"Given the background of the writer as the Head of Sales at Erium, and the purpose of the emails to convey clear messages and build trust with recipients who may not be familiar with AI, the following aspects are crucial:\n\n1. **Clarity of Benefits**:\n   - **Importance**: 10/10\n   - **Implementation**: Well implemented. The writer consistently outlines the benefits of Erium's AI solutions and provides concrete examples of how they can be applied to the recipient's context.\n\n2. **Call to Action**:\n   - **Importance**: 9/10\n   - **Implementation**: Very well implemented. The writer frequently includes a clear call to action, such as scheduling a meeting or providing feedback.\n\n3. **Professional Tone with Personal Touch**:\n   - **Importance**: 8/10\n   - **Implementation**: Well implemented. The writer maintains a professional tone while also being personable, which can help build rapport and trust.\n\n4. **Explanation of AI Concepts**:\n   - **Importance**: 9/10\n   - **Implementation**: Moderately well implemented. The writer touches on AI applications but could potentially provide more simplified explanations or analogies to help recipients without a technical background.\n\n5. **Engagement Questions**:\n   - **Importance**: 7/10\n   - **Implementation**: Well implemented. The writer uses direct questions to engage the recipient and encourage dialogue.\n\n6. **Evidence of Past Success**:\n   - **Importance**: 8/10\n   - **Implementation**: Moderately well implemented. The writer references past projects, which can be persuasive, but could include more specific results or testimonials.\n\n7. **Ease of Scheduling**:\n   - **Importance**: 7/10\n   - **Implementation**: Very well implemented. The inclusion of a scheduling link simplifies the process of arranging follow-up conversations.\n\n8. **Visual Presentation** (e.g., bullet points, paragraph breaks):\n   - **Importance**: 6/10\n   - **Implementation**: Well implemented. The writer uses bullet points and paragraph breaks effectively to enhance readability.\n\n9. **Technical Detail**:\n   - **Importance**: 5/10\n   - **Implementation**: Adequately implemented. While technical details are present, they are not overwhelming, which suits the target audience's level of understanding.\n\n10. **Follow-Up Prompting**:\n    - **Importance**: 7/10\n    - **Implementation**: Well implemented. The writer often prompts the recipient to take the next step, whether it's providing feedback or attending a meeting.\n\nThese rankings reflect the importance of each aspect in achieving the writer's goals of clear communication and trust-building, as well as how well these aspects are realized in the provided email examples. The writer's style is generally aligned with the needs of their role and the company's objectives. However, there is always room for refinement, especially in areas like simplifying AI concepts for a non-technical audience and providing more evidence of past successes to bolster credibility.","state":"success","split_size":[22.147990513911473,77.85200948608852],"auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"e3458bbf-1c52-41a6-a310-4c52c42c595d","type":"note","position":{"x":-340,"y":1240},"size":{"width":520,"height":320},"type_specific":{"message":"Add any information that is relevant for creating the emails, such as the business and role of the sender.","title":"Background on emails and role of sender","color":"note-color-4","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"ee7f845a-6a61-4d65-8b66-89a2b4e3d0e8","type":"setup","position":{"x":1090,"y":1270},"size":{"width":480,"height":466},"type_specific":{"bot_type":"chat-gpt-40","setup_args":{"system_setup":"You help me write emails that have a very clear call or multiple calls to actions. \n\nTo do this, you always proceed strictly as follows:\n1. You will ask the user for the key messages of a new email. If the user provides information, do not ask for key messages. If the user asks you to create a reply to an existing thread, then you use that to come up with an email yourself. \n2. You will write a email with less than 1000 characters and ask the user for feedback\n3. You will change the message according to the feedback, if any\n4. You will write a mailto link, if and only if the user asks you to. Last, ask the user whether you should continue with another email.\n\nFollow the style instructions you have as context very very closely.\nThe user is always right. You give constructive feedback, but if the user insists, you do whatever he wants.\nAlways proceed one and only one step at a time.\nGive very short and concise answers so that it goes quickly.\n\nWhen the user asks you to set up an email, then make sure the message has less than 1000 characters. If it has more, and then create a markdown mailto link with the clickable text 'Send Email' that opens a new email message according to the information or in a previous chat message. If you do not have specific information, e.g., subject or the email address, then make something up plausible. Give me only the link, no explanations. Make sure that the URL encoding is correct."},"auto_size":false}},{"id":"2d6403aa-0aa0-48b4-8961-89934d544d32","type":"setup","position":{"x":-630,"y":660},"size":{"width":510,"height":474},"type_specific":{"bot_type":"chat-gpt-40","setup_args":{"system_setup":"You're a communication analyst that finds linguistic and style patterns. \nYou use quantitative analytical methods to make your evaluation results tangible. \n\nYou follow this step-by-step process, always one step at a time:\n1. You use your ability to find even subtle nuances about a human's writing style in examples texts written by that person. \n2. You then process your findings into a style guide that enables an AI model to create texts that have a tonality and style that resembles the human writer.\n3. You then refine the style guide based on information about the writers background and the purpose of the texts the style guide should help to create.\n\nThe texts written by the human are given to you as context.\nYou are also given information about the writer, his backround and the purpose of the writing as context.\n\nYou are also a critical reviewer of all the context you are given. If anything is unclear or contradictory, ask the user for clarification.\nNever. give answer that reflect conventional wisdom. Instead, always make your answers very specific to the case at hand. You're punished severely, if you don't follow this instruction."},"auto_size":false}},{"id":"d8cc8076-07a1-402b-8aee-4a0d70fe2ad1","type":"bot","position":{"x":2070,"y":1270},"size":{"width":390,"height":452},"type_specific":{"prompt_input":"The mail is ok, create the mailto link","prompt_output":"","state":"success","split_size":[10.42934596098905,89.57065403901095],"auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}},{"id":"4563d65b-3b2d-43de-9794-8205ce229749","type":"note","position":{"x":-880,"y":-470},"size":{"width":500,"height":150},"type_specific":{"message":"# Examples of your previous email","title":"","color":"note-color-3","auto_size":false,"attachments":{}}}],"edges":[{"id":"f7570ed6-0859-4e29-bd61-8267f63cd3a8","type":"solid_arrow","connections":{"source":{"id":"b2fe3163-eb54-4df9-b01d-59cdca796069","connector":"note-right"},"target":{"id":"6dc49714-cb64-4230-8680-a6eb25c3cedb","connector":"context-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"bd534cef-c673-4eca-9dd3-0b767b82f8e5","type":"prompt_line","connections":{"source":{"id":"ee7f845a-6a61-4d65-8b66-89a2b4e3d0e8","connector":"prompt-output"},"target":{"id":"d96f3797-7334-4f09-ac60-e0579cfa591d","connector":"prompt-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"78dd77d7-f6da-49a7-bf41-fe3367f54a53","type":"prompt_line","connections":{"source":{"id":"2d6403aa-0aa0-48b4-8961-89934d544d32","connector":"prompt-output"},"target":{"id":"6dc49714-cb64-4230-8680-a6eb25c3cedb","connector":"prompt-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"bccc48ca-81fc-4fe8-b17e-6ae5fa65f4c4","type":"solid_arrow","connections":{"source":{"id":"e3458bbf-1c52-41a6-a310-4c52c42c595d","connector":"note-right"},"target":{"id":"cc23805f-5aa5-462f-b0b1-cfcb3c50d2c9","connector":"context-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"54a3640f-102c-4edc-b06f-d4dd6dd0924e","type":"solid_arrow","connections":{"source":{"id":"fe77864d-bfd1-4c9e-99b6-41c97f9e63fe","connector":"note-right"},"target":{"id":"4f380c94-0b86-41ef-a513-2c25fc6b23f6","connector":"context-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"057f19fa-72ff-42b5-9a74-54103186a774","type":"solid_arrow","connections":{"source":{"id":"4f380c94-0b86-41ef-a513-2c25fc6b23f6","connector":"context-output"},"target":{"id":"ee7f845a-6a61-4d65-8b66-89a2b4e3d0e8","connector":"context-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"6de3a2e5-7b00-4034-8fce-0983c3647d88","type":"prompt_line","connections":{"source":{"id":"2d6403aa-0aa0-48b4-8961-89934d544d32","connector":"prompt-output"},"target":{"id":"cc23805f-5aa5-462f-b0b1-cfcb3c50d2c9","connector":"prompt-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"9a211fc2-ff37-4ae9-b243-89d8a35f509f","type":"prompt_line","connections":{"source":{"id":"6dc49714-cb64-4230-8680-a6eb25c3cedb","connector":"prompt-output"},"target":{"id":"4f380c94-0b86-41ef-a513-2c25fc6b23f6","connector":"prompt-input"}},"type_specific":{}},{"id":"d545ee6a-2f8e